  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The country is on fire - Vimal Weerawansa",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government led by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe lacks confidence at the national and international levels. The country is on fire.",
        "Realizing the seriousness of the crisis, all political parties should come together to establish an all-party government, Vimal Weerawansa, the leader of the National Freedom Front, urged in the assembly.",
        "He mentioned the above while presenting a special statement when the Parliament met on Monday (04) under the chairmanship of the Speaker.",
        "Parliament does not meet under normal circumstances. The country is under self-imposed lockdown. Lanka IOC The fuel line in front of the filling station stretches for several kilometers every day.",
        "The Prime Minister and the Power Minister did not allow the House to answer the questions raised regarding the crisis in fuel and essential services.",
        "The country is heading towards a worst crisis. It should be noted that there is no worse crisis than the current situation.",
        "The international community has no faith in Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe. No one is going to have faith in a person who was ignored by the people and elected to the parliament through the national list and got the post of Prime Minister.",
        "There is no trust in the government at the national level and at the international level, so considering the serious nature of the current situation, all political parties should come together to establish an all-party government under the instructions of Mahanayake Theras.",
        "Question-and-answer period in Parliament and conducting counter-arguments will not solve the current problems of the social structure. He said the President is ignorant of the problems facing the people.",
        "The Speaker said that it is not a current issue, mention it in a separate speech.",
        "Don't mention it, don't mention it because you have fuel. People are facing the worst crisis. No plans have been presented so far to provide satisfactory relief to the people.",
        "As we are in the opposition, we are not going to try to achieve narrow objectives through the present situation. If we want to solve the problems, we will make individual efforts. Unfortunately, the present government does not have the trust of the international community.",
        "The country is on fire. All parties need to come together to solve the problems. Staying in a bad position and talking about unnecessary issues will only intensify the crisis.",
        "During this, Chief Minister Dinesh Gunawardena, who interrupted and commented, decided the order of the meeting of the council for the decision of all the party leaders. We did not decide the council proceedings personally.",
        "The fuel crisis has intensified. None of the ministers are given fuel personally. We also get fuel from the line. We can take forward the discussion regarding the fuel issue under the leadership of the Speaker, he said.",
        "This was followed by unrest in the House as the ruling and opposition parties rose from their seats and demanded an opportunity to address.",
        "The Speaker informed the House that, 'Members, cooperate with the decision of the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs to carry forward today's proceedings and address other matters separately.",
        "What will the people of the country think about the activities of the parliament.",
        "Vimal Weerawansa mentioned that our responsibility is to show that the parliament is insensitive and we should pay attention to all the parties working together to solve the current crisis."
      ],
